Scribimus, inclusus] “ We shut our- selves up and write (one verse, another prose), something grand for the lungs, most bountiful of breath to puff and blow.'’ [Jahn has ‘ Scribimus inclusi.'] He goes on to describe a man reciting his produc- tions (see Juv. i. 1, n.; vii. 39, sqq.),with his hair smoothed and trimmed, his toga fresh cleaned, with his best (birthday) ring on, sitting on a raised stool, his throat well garg-led, and a leer in his eye, showing the lewd character of his composition :—
